"i dont know how to break this news to anyone... especially si-games.. if they are even interested enough to read these reviews. but .. well i sort of rolled into fm back in 2010... which is not as long ago as some of you, but long enough to make a valid opinion i think. i really do am glad that the time of cardboard public around the field is history, believe me. i usually play fm when i wake up.. and am in no way, shape, or form, capable to play any action game whatsoever, being as old as i am... so i love to start my day with fm... to each his own right ?... you should know... i once was a rather fanatical ajax fan.. started out at 7 years old... but those times are over since 1997... ajax utterly ruined that... and destroyed their true fans in the process.. i still love the game though.. eventhough these days... it seems to me more like a bussiness with emplyees, then a a club with club-honor, and real die-hard fans. ... and sorry to say... fm mirrors that a bit... but let me tell you first of all.. i hate mandatory. something from my youth no doubt. and the mandatory team chat of fm14 was a sharp pain to live with... i usually did those with my eyes closed, and got out at the first chance i got... not even knowing what i just said i wanted to hear... now.. in fm15.. when you finally have a first team together that plays well.. like each other, win more games then they lose... chances are that some damn snot-nose from the second or 3rd team comes asking for first-team foortball.. sigh. you look at his stats and just laugh.... i have been a footballer myself, some time ago, obviously... on quite a high level even, mind you.. even played for ajax a few weeks... before i failed the medical... but i wouldnt have dared go to the first team manager and ask him to be in his team or.... ill be unhappy ?...... ha.. he would recommend me to cry a while on my mommys lap.. or if that wouldnt be good enough... give me the number of a good shrink, and send me off with a slap on the back of my head... and quite rightly so... in past fm games i never gave them the time of day.. if anyone was any good, his own trainer or my chief schout would tip me of on his existence or progress... and that was it... now.. in fm15.. it is mandatory to speak to this snotnose... really ?.... and if i decline.. half my team will be saying that i handled him unfairfly... so gone balance, gone ... arggghhh..., and then i havent told you about, that if you have a really important game.. 90% chance your best striker will tear a muscle on the trainings field.. one or two days before the match... and will be unavailable... for 3 bloody months. have i told you yet how many times one of our stikers is offside in one single game ?... 10723548303-times... thats how many.. now... i seen enough games.. been to games... played enough games... to know that this is utterly unrealistic at best.. and plain imposible usually... if my midielder launches a long ranged shot... it comes back from the opposite team keeper who could only parry it... and my striker scores from the rebound... it is not offside.... thats a blatant lie... the whisle goes, and the comments say the whisle had already gone.... no .. it did not... it just went... so even if my striker was offside, your bloody whistle should have been going the second the ball left my midfielders foot... not a minute later when my stiker scores the rebound... you incompetent . besides... half my players look like in albinos... white as snow... very irritating... also players warp all over the field on occasion... which is rather immercive breaking, up to the point where it is rediculus... i know... you can not win all games.. that should be obvious to anyone... (unless you cheat) but when spirits are high, moods at at top level... every one in the team is top fit and inspired to win... there is no bloody way, that my team suddenly cant play anymore... passes wrong, misses headers, gets yellow and red cards all over the place... there is no.. bloody... way.... sure.. even with everything good and in place... then we could still lose the game.. it happens... but not with a team that looked like i just fielded a 3rd team of incompetant todlers.. that seemed completely incapable to even hit a ball.. let alone pass it right... okay.... those who know me, know i will always give you the truth as i see it... which, obviously, isnt the ultimate truth... what is ?.... but.... after having played fm15 for as long as it is out... and having played fm10 -fm11 - fm12 - fm13 and fm14 to death... i simply cannot recommend fm15 and live with myself. i love this game.., i really do... but i hate fm15.. still.. i do not regret buying it, simply because i have gotten so much pleasure out of the previous installments that i dont mind giving the folks at si some donation... but i think i will go back to fm14.. and hope fm16 will be better.... or maybe.. even fm15 with some patching... who knows ?.... but as things stand.. i can not recomend this version of football manager to anyone... unless you are a masocist.. so.. i am sorry si.. but i simply can not.. guys and girls.. do yourself a faviour.. stay on fm14 .. or if you are new to this game... buy fm14.. not fm15.. trust me.. you wont regret it... fm15 is one long big pester campaign... made to ruin your day completely... it is in no way any fun... and it will put you off on one of the best, if not the best football manager simulation games around... i am sorry to say. (edit) the latest patches have really done some good to this game... i can now sometimes stomach it sometimes... if not too long... ill keep fm14 installed for now.... but.... keep up the good work si.. and maybe one day i might have to change my review to a more positive recomendation... one can only hope...",163.1
